        • [ - ] CirdomAkul - member since 18-Sep-15

          Spurs played a fantastic game. The only problem I saw was defending Dembele and Coutinho. Dembele is a kind of player that can run into any space with the ball. You just shouldn't allow him to start running with the ball. Easier said that done of course but the problem was no player tried to put pressure on him seconds before he got the ball. The worst part was he ended up moving between the midfielders and defenders and that caused lots of problems. Similar problem with Coutinho. He has this trademark move that whenever he is on the ball, he tends to cut on his right or shoot a curved shot to his right. That's the most dangerous thing he could do and you simply should prioritize to prevent it as a defender. Toby kept moving back with him especially near the box which is very bad defending in my opinion. Defending is truly an art and is underrated in my opinion.
